Package swp_compiler_ss13.fuc.parser.grammar

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Grammar
    This class represents a context free grammar consisting of Terminals, Productions and NonTerminals.
    GrammarSpec
    This is a helper class for defining Grammars directly in Java.
    NonTerminal
    Like all Symbols NonTerminals are identified by their String id, except NonTerminal.SpecialNonTerminal!
    NonTerminal.SpecialNonTerminal  
    Production
    A production consists of a left hand side NonTerminal and a list of right hand side Symbols.
    ProjectGrammar
    This classes define our grammar as specified in the requirements for the separate milestones
    ProjectGrammar.Complete  
    ProjectGrammar.M1  
    Symbol
    The base class for both Terminal and NonTerminal, which are identified by their Symbol.SymbolType and Symbol.id.
    Terminal
    Like all Symbols Terminals are identified by their String id, except Terminal.SpecialTerminal!
    Terminal.SpecialTerminal  
    TokenEx
    This class wraps a Token and adds a Terminal as specified in the Grammar, as the parser internally needs the association Token -> Terminal.
    TokenEx.BoolTokenEx  
    TokenEx.NumTokenEx  
    TokenEx.RealTokenEx
